# PLAYHUB — React & Next.js Patterns

## Server vs Client
```tsx
// ✅ Server Component (default) — data fetching, layouts, static content
export default async function VenuePage({ params }: Props) {
  const venue = await getVenue(params.id);
  return <VenueDetails venue={venue} />;
}

// ✅ Client Component — only when needed
"use client";
export function SlotPicker({ slots }: { slots: Slot[] }) { ... }
```

## Feature modules
```
src/features/booking/
  components/   # Feature-specific UI
  hooks/        # useSlots, useBookingRealtime
  actions/      # Server actions
  index.ts      # Public exports only
```

## Components
- Reuse `src/components/ui/` (Shadcn) before creating new primitives
- Colocate feature components in `src/features/{name}/components/`
- Export via `index.ts`; avoid deep imports across features

## Forms
```tsx
"use client";
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";
import { zodResolver } from "@hookform/resolvers/zod";
import { bookingSchema } from "@/lib/validators/booking.schema";

const form = useForm({ resolver: zodResolver(bookingSchema) });
```

## Performance
- Paginate all lists; avoid fetching unbounded data
- Use React Query for client cache (when module requires it)
- Dynamic import heavy client libs (Leaflet, Recharts)
- `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` only when cookies/auth required
